[
    {
        "content": "<p>Hi everyone!</p>\n<p><span class=\"user-mention\" data-user-id=\"758058\">@Rob Herring</span>  and I have been hitting a small issue when we want to fill in <code>compatible</code> for <code>of_device_id</code> from a user-supplied <code>BStr</code>:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Rust\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"cm\">/*</span>\n<span class=\"cm\"> * Struct used for matching a device</span>\n<span class=\"cm\"> */</span>\n<span class=\"k\">struct</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">of_device_id</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"kt\">char</span><span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">name</span><span class=\"p\">[</span><span class=\"mi\">32</span><span class=\"p\">];</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"kt\">char</span><span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"k\">type</span><span class=\"p\">[</span><span class=\"mi\">32</span><span class=\"p\">];</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"kt\">char</span><span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">compatible</span><span class=\"p\">[</span><span class=\"mi\">128</span><span class=\"p\">];</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"k\">const</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">void</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">*</span><span class=\"n\">data</span><span class=\"p\">;</span>\n<span class=\"p\">};</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>This field gets converted by bindgen into <code>[i8; 128]</code>, while a BStr can dereference to <code>&amp;[u8]</code>. </p>\n<p>Due to the different types (<code>i8</code> vs <code>u8</code>), <code>copy_from_slice()</code> does not work. I don't see a more straightforward way other than copying byte by byte with a loop, using <code>as</code> to cast:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Rust\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"k\">pub</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">const</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">fn</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">new</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">compatible</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kp\">&amp;</span><span class=\"nc\">BStr</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">-&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">Self</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"kd\">let</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">mut</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">i</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">0</span><span class=\"p\">;</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"kd\">let</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">mut</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">compat</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">[</span><span class=\"kt\">i8</span><span class=\"p\">;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">128</span><span class=\"p\">]</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">[</span><span class=\"mi\">0</span><span class=\"p\">;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">128</span><span class=\"p\">];</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"k\">while</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">i</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">compatible</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">len</span><span class=\"p\">()</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">            </span><span class=\"c1\">// If `compatible` does not fit in `id.compatible`, an \"index out of bounds\" build time</span>\n<span class=\"w\">            </span><span class=\"c1\">// error will be triggered.</span>\n<span class=\"w\">            </span><span class=\"n\">compat</span><span class=\"p\">[</span><span class=\"n\">i</span><span class=\"p\">]</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">compatible</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">deref_const</span><span class=\"p\">()[</span><span class=\"n\">i</span><span class=\"p\">]</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">as</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">_</span><span class=\"p\">;</span>\n<span class=\"w\">            </span><span class=\"n\">i</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">+=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">1</span><span class=\"p\">;</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"p\">}</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"n\">compat</span><span class=\"p\">[</span><span class=\"n\">i</span><span class=\"p\">]</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"sc\">b'\\0'</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">as</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">_</span><span class=\"p\">;</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"bp\">Self</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">bindings</span><span class=\"p\">::</span><span class=\"n\">of_device_id</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">            </span><span class=\"n\">name</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">[</span><span class=\"mi\">0</span><span class=\"p\">;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">32</span><span class=\"p\">],</span>\n<span class=\"w\">            </span><span class=\"n\">type_</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">[</span><span class=\"mi\">0</span><span class=\"p\">;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">32</span><span class=\"p\">],</span>\n<span class=\"w\">            </span><span class=\"n\">compatible</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">compat</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n<span class=\"w\">            </span><span class=\"n\">data</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">core</span><span class=\"p\">::</span><span class=\"n\">ptr</span><span class=\"p\">::</span><span class=\"n\">null</span><span class=\"p\">(),</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"p\">})</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"p\">}</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>I wonder whether anyone else can think of a better idea? Also, IIRC, <span class=\"user-mention\" data-user-id=\"413824\">@Gary Guo</span> was working on a prototype to map <code>char</code> to <code>u8</code>, which would make this simpler.</p>\n<p>Thanks!</p>",
        "id": 477484977,
        "sender_full_name": "Daniel Almeida",
        "timestamp": 1729183498
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Ideally, you would just use Gary's patches that changes <code>char</code> to <code>u8</code>: <a href=\"https://lore.kernel.org/rust-for-linux/20240913213041.395655-1-gary@garyguo.net/\">https://lore.kernel.org/rust-for-linux/20240913213041.395655-1-gary@garyguo.net/</a></p>",
        "id": 477486050,
        "sender_full_name": "Benno Lossin",
        "timestamp": 1729183874
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>but I don't know if they are \"production-ready\" yet :)</p>",
        "id": 477486080,
        "sender_full_name": "Benno Lossin",
        "timestamp": 1729183886
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I seem to be stepping into all sorts of sign issues today. I converted some C code to this:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Rust\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">bindings</span><span class=\"p\">::</span><span class=\"n\">capable</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">uapi</span><span class=\"p\">::</span><span class=\"n\">CAP_SYS_NICE</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>That doesn't work because the #define is made unsigned and capable() takes a signed value. The compiler provides the fix, but \"uapi::CAP_SYS_NICE.try_into().unwrap()\" everywhere seems less than ideal...</p>",
        "id": 477489176,
        "sender_full_name": "Rob Herring",
        "timestamp": 1729185038
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"582628\">Daniel Almeida</span> <a href=\"#narrow/channel/291565-Help/topic/Converting.20from.20.26.5Bu8.5D.20to.20.5Bi8.3B.20128.5D.20in.20struct.20of_device_id/near/477484977\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"758058\">Rob Herring</span>  and I have been hitting a small issue when we want to fill in <code>compatible</code> for <code>of_device_id</code> from a user-supplied <code>BStr</code>:</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>Are you aware of <a href=\"https://github.com/AsahiLinux/linux/blob/asahi/rust/kernel/of.rs#L77\">https://github.com/AsahiLinux/linux/blob/asahi/rust/kernel/of.rs#L77</a>? It uses a loop as well ...</p>",
        "id": 477505418,
        "sender_full_name": "Dirk Behme",
        "timestamp": 1729191300
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"669329\">Dirk Behme</span> <a href=\"#narrow/channel/291565-Help/topic/Converting.20from.20.26.5Bu8.5D.20to.20.5Bi8.3B.20128.5D.20in.20struct.20of_device_id/near/477505418\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"582628\">Daniel Almeida</span> <a href=\"#narrow/channel/291565-Help/topic/Converting.20from.20.26.5Bu8.5D.20to.20.5Bi8.3B.20128.5D.20in.20struct.20of_device_id/near/477484977\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"758058\">Rob Herring</span>  and I have been hitting a small issue when we want to fill in <code>compatible</code> for <code>of_device_id</code> from a user-supplied <code>BStr</code>:</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>Are you aware of <a href=\"https://github.com/AsahiLinux/linux/blob/asahi/rust/kernel/of.rs#L77\">https://github.com/AsahiLinux/linux/blob/asahi/rust/kernel/of.rs#L77</a>? It uses a loop as well ...</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>Yes, notice the comment is exactly the same. That's what I'm updating to 6.12 and the DeviceId changes in nova-next. It doesn't seem ideal, but I ended keeping that for now. That loop is about the only thing that's left unchanged from the Asahi version.</p>",
        "id": 477508801,
        "sender_full_name": "Rob Herring",
        "timestamp": 1729192520
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"758058\">Rob Herring</span> <a href=\"#narrow/channel/291565-Help/topic/Converting.20from.20.26.5Bu8.5D.20to.20.5Bi8.3B.20128.5D.20in.20struct.20of_device_id/near/477508801\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>It doesn't seem ideal, but I ended keeping that for now. That loop is about the only thing that's left unchanged from the Asahi version.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>Do you have any plans mainlining device tree abstractions?</p>",
